Deputy Minister of Police Maggie Sotyu says that she is shocked following the murders of three women in separate attacks in Cape Town. CAPE TOWN - Deputy Minister of Police Maggie Sotyu says she's shocked following the murders of three women in separate attacks in Cape Town over the past few days.On Sunday, the body of Noluvo Swelindawo was found under a bridge along the N2 highway near Khayelitsha.We fail Black lesbians every single day with our silence. How many more lives must be lost? #NoluvoSwelindawoShe'd been shot, allegedly because she was a lesbian.Thembeka Dumani was shot and killed in the Marikana informal settlement in Philippi East.#FemaleMurders #16DaysOfActivism Thembeka Dumani was shot and killed in the Marikana Informal Settlement in Philippi East. LIIn Khayelitsha, Nopinki Fuba's body was found dumped near a communal toilet in Site B.Her boyfriend has been arrested and Sotyu attended his court appearance on Thursday. It s unbelievable that these murders occurred during the 16 Days of Activism for No Violence against Women and Children campaign. What s more painful is the fact that they were been killed by the people that they know, trust and supposed to be loving them. #FemaleMurders #16DaysOfActivism In Khayelitsha, Nopinki Fuba&#39;s body was found dumped near a communal toilet in Site B.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)